/* v0.6 Tier 7 — en-US bundle for SwiftUI's LocalizedStringKey auto-resolution.
 *
 * SwiftUI's `Text("Foo")`, `Label("Foo", ...)`, `Button("Foo") { ... }` etc.
 * use the `LocalizedStringKey` overload when given a string literal, which
 * looks up the literal as a key in this file at render time. Keys here
 * mirror the literal English strings used at the call site one-for-one.
 *
 * Adding a translation = adding a new `<locale>.lproj/Localizable.strings`
 * next to this one with matching keys and translated values. The keys here
 * are the source of truth — keep them in sync with `Text("…")` literals in
 * the Sources tree.
 *
 * Strings that need runtime parameterization (counts, percentages, file
 * names) use `%@` / `%lld` / `%.2f` format specifiers and are looked up via
 * `String(localized:defaultValue:)` or `String(format: NSLocalizedString(…))`
 * at the call site — see ProjectListView, TimelineArea, AddSFXSheet.
 */

